er who studied the effects of hormones like testosterone and estradiol on the limbic system and their influence on aggressive and sexual behaviors in animals in 1989.", "MEDNICK:Mednick is a researcher who conducted comparative studies showing that adolescents with antisocial behavior exhibit low autonomic reactivity, such as slow heart rate and quick recovery from stimuli, which may impair their ability to learn to avoid punishment.", "THALAMUS:The thalamus is a brain region involved in sensory and motor signal relay, and its anterior part has been studied in relation to aggressive and sexual behaviors in animals."], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}